Wash and dry all produce. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @red onion{1}(halved, peeled, and sliced); mince a
few slices until you have 2 TBSP (3 TBSP for 4 servings). Halve, core, and thinly slice
@poblano pepper{1}(halved, cored, and thinly sliced) into strips. Dice @roma tomato{1}(diced). Zest and
quarter @lime{1}(zested and quartered) (quarter both limes for 4).

In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, 1¼ cups water (2¼ cups for 4 servings), and
@salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender,
~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add
poblano and sliced onion. Cook, stirring occasionally, until softened and lightly charred,
~{8-10%minutes}. Season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}
and cover to keep warm. Wipe out pan.

While veggies cook, in a #small bowl{}, combine minced onion, tomato, and a squeeze of lime juice
to taste. Season with salt and pepper. In a separate small bowl, combine @sour cream{2%tbsp} and
a squeeze of lime juice to taste. Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling
consistency. Season with salt and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for veggies over medium-high heat. Add @ground beef{10%oz} and
cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Stir in
@tomato paste{1.5%oz}, @Southwest spice blend{1%tbsp}, and ¼ cup water (⅓ cup for 4 servings).
Cook, scraping up any browned bits from bottom of pan, until mixture is thickened and saucy,
~{1-2%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

> TIP: If there's excess grease in your pan, carefully pour it out.

Fluff rice with a #fork{} and stir in lime zest and @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings).
Season with salt and pepper. Divide between #bowls{} and top with beef mixture, veggies,
@Monterey Jack cheese{1/4%cup}, and pico de gallo. Drizzle with crema and dollop with
@guacamole{4%tbsp}. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.